
[1]detach

   DETACH, v.t. [See Attach.]

   1. To separate or disunite; to disengage; to part from; as, to detach
   the coats of a bulbous root from each other; to detach a man from the
   interest of the minister, or from a party.

   2. To separate men from their companies or regiments; to draw from
   companies or regiments, as a party of men, and send them on a
   particular service.

   3. To select ships from a fleet and send them on a separate service.
